<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! \import pragma

Pulls functions/procedures from tiddlers into scope. Used for mixin composition (last-wins semantics).

!! \parameters

Declares tiddler-level parameters with defaults. Facades use this for their public API.

!! $transclude modes

* `$transclude $tiddler=""` — creates new transclusion boundary (slot/fill works)
* `$transclude $variable=""` — does NOT create boundary (slot may not find fill)

!! $slot / $fill

* Insert content at predefined points in templates
* ''Critical limitation'': no colons in `$name` (fails silently) — use hyphens
* ''Critical limitation'': `$slot` in `\procedure` doesn't find `$fill` from `$transclude $tiddler=`
* Workaround: body-level `$slot` with `<%if%>` branching
* Why pills works: intermediate `core/menu` tiddler transclusion creates boundary

!! $eventcatcher

Catches click events matching CSS selectors. Sets `dom-data-*` variables from `data-*` attributes on clicked elements.

!! <%if%>

Conditional rendering widget. Used in vtabs for type-based branching at body level.

!! code-body: yes

Field that tells TW to treat tiddler body as `\function`/`\procedure`/`\parameters` definitions.

!! is[variable]

Filter operator that checks if a variable/function is defined in current scope.

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="danger">
<$fill $name="body">Never use colons in `$slot`/`$fill` `$name` attributes (e.g., `$name="view:sco"`). TW silently fails — no error, just falls back to default content. Use hyphens instead: `$name="view-sco"`.</$fill>
</$transclude>

</$fill>
</$transclude>
